=======================================================

60e3a7f3c: Fri Mar 13 19:59:49 2015 +0100 Tom Reijnders
Fixed #196 and #219

- All media types don't have an inline editor anymore
- All inputtext types by default have no inline editor anymore
- All inputtext fields where the new attribute wysiwyg="true"is switched
  on, do have an inline editor
- media with an url enclosed in '' work again
- you don't have to quote the url anymore, you can paste the url directly

=======================================================

ff7de5a26: Fri Mar 13 19:59:49 2015 +0100 Tom Reijnders
Fixed #196 and #219

- All media types don't have an inline editor anymore
- All inputtext types by default have no inline editor anymore
- All inputtext fields where the new attribute wysiwyg="true"is switched
  on, do have an inline editor
- media with an url enclosed in '' work again
- you don't have to quote the url anymore, you can paste the url directly

=======================================================

